  nickname: amo
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: The words of Amos, who was among the sheepbreeders of Tekoa, which
        he saw concerning Israel in the days of Uzziah king of Judah, and in the
        days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, two years before the earthquake.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Judgment on the Nations'
      title: Judgment on the Nations
      number: 2
      content: "And he said:\u201CThe Lord  roars from Zion,And utters His voice
        from Jerusalem;The pastures of the shepherds mourn,And the top of Carmel
        withers.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Damascus, and
        for four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they have threshed Gilead
        with implements of iron."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But I will send a fire into the house of Hazael,Which shall devour
        the palaces of Ben-Hadad.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I will also break the gate  bar of Damascus,And cut off the inhabitant
        from the Valley of Aven,And the one who holds the scepter from Beth Eden.The
        people of Syria shall go captive to Kir,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Gaza, and for
        four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they took captive the whole
        captivityTo deliver them up to Edom."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But I will send a fire upon the wall of Gaza,Which shall devour its
        palaces.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will cut off the inhabitant from Ashdod,And the one who holds the
        scepter from Ashkelon;I will turn My hand against Ekron,And the remnant of
        the Philistines shall perish,\u201DSays the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Tyre, and for
        four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they delivered up the whole
        captivity to Edom,And did not remember the covenant of brotherhood."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But I will send a fire upon the wall of Tyre,Which shall devour its
        palaces.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Edom, and for
        four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because he pursued his brother with
        the sword,And cast off all pity;His anger tore perpetually,And he kept his
        wrath forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But I will send a fire upon Teman,Which shall devour the palaces
        of Bozrah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of the people of
        Ammon, and for four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they ripped
        open the women with child in Gilead,That they might enlarge their territory."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But I will kindle a fire in the wall of Rabbah,And it shall devour
        its palaces,Amid shouting in the day of battle,And a tempest in the day of
        the whirlwind.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Their king shall go into captivity,He and his princes together,\u201DSays
        the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Moab, and for
        four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because he burned the bones of the
        king of Edom to lime."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: But I will send a fire upon Moab,And it shall devour the palaces of
        Kerioth;Moab shall die with tumult,With shouting and trumpet sound.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Judgment on Judah'
      title: Judgment on Judah
      number: 3
      content: "And I will cut off the judge from its midst,And slay all its princes
        with him,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Judah, and for
        four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they have despised the law
        of the Lord,And have not kept His commandments.Their lies lead them astray,Lies 
        which their fathers followed."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Judgment on Israel'
      title: Judgment on Israel
      number: 5
      content: "But I will send a fire upon Judah,And it shall devour the palaces
        of Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CFor three transgressions of Israel, and
        for four,I will not turn away its punishment,Because they sell the righteous
        for silver,And the poor for a pair of sandals."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They pant after the dust of the earth which  is on the head of the
        poor,And pervert the way of the humble.A man and his father go in to the
        same girl,To defile My holy name.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They lie down by every altar on clothes taken in pledge,And drink
        the wine of the condemned in the house of their god.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYet it  was I who destroyed the Amorite before them,Whose height
        was like the height of the cedars,And he was  as strong as the oaks;Yet I
        destroyed his fruit aboveAnd his roots beneath."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Also it  was  I who brought you up from the land of Egypt,And led
        you forty years through the wilderness,To possess the land of the Amorite.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I raised up some of your sons as prophets,And some of your young
        men as Nazirites.Is  it not so, O you children of Israel?\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut you gave the Nazirites wine to drink,And commanded the
        prophets saying,\u2018Do not prophesy!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am weighed down by you,As a cart full of sheaves
        is weighed down."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Therefore flight shall perish from the swift,The strong shall not
        strengthen his power,Nor shall the mighty deliver himself;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He shall not stand who handles the bow,The swift of foot shall not
        escape,Nor shall he who rides a horse deliver himself.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The most courageous men of mightShall flee naked in that day,\u201DSays
        the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Authority of the Prophet\u2019s Message"
      title: "Authority of the Prophet\u2019s Message"
      number: 1
      content: 'Hear this word that the Lord has spoken against you, O children of
        Israel, against the whole family which I brought up from the land of Egypt,
        saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYou only have I known of all the families of the earth;Therefore
        I will punish you for all your iniquities.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Can two walk together, unless they are agreed?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Will a lion roar in the forest, when he has no prey?Will a young lion
        cry out of his den, if he has caught nothing?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Will a bird fall into a snare on the earth, where there is no trap
        for it?Will a snare spring up from the earth, if it has caught nothing at
        all?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: If a trumpet is blown in a city, will not the people be afraid?If
        there is calamity in a city, will not the Lord have done it?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Surely the Lord God does nothing,Unless He reveals His secret to His
        servants the prophets.
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Punishment of Israel\u2019s Sins"
      title: "Punishment of Israel\u2019s Sins"
      number: 8
      content: A lion has roared!Who will not fear?The Lord God has spoken!Who can
        but prophesy?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CProclaim in the palaces at Ashdod,And in the palaces in the
        land of Egypt, and say:\u2018Assemble on the mountains of Samaria;See great
        tumults in her midst,And the oppressed within her."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For they do not know to do right,\u2019Says the Lord,\u2018Who store
        up violence and robbery in their palaces.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CAn adversary shall  be all
        around the land;He shall sap your strength from you,And your palaces shall
        be plundered.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CAs a shepherd takes from the mouth of a
        lionTwo legs or a piece of an ear,So shall the children of Israel be taken
        outWho dwell in Samaria\u2014In the corner of a bed and on the edge of a
        couch!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Hear and testify against the house of Jacob,\u201DSays the Lord God,
        the God of hosts,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThat in the day I punish Israel for their transgressions,I
        will also visit destruction on the altars of Bethel;And the horns of the
        altar shall be cut offAnd fall to the ground."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will destroy the winter house along with the summer house;The houses
        of ivory shall perish,And the great houses shall have an end,\u201DSays the
        Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Hear this word, you cows of Bashan, who are on the mountain of Samaria,Who
        oppress the poor,Who crush the needy,Who say to your husbands, \u201CBring
        wine, let us drink!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord God has sworn by His holiness:\u201CBehold, the days shall
        come upon youWhen He will take you away with fishhooks,And your posterity
        with fishhooks."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You will go out through broken walls,Each one straight ahead of her,And
        you will be cast into Harmon,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome to Bethel and transgress,At Gilgal multiply transgression;Bring
        your sacrifices every morning,Your tithes every three days."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Did Not Accept Correction'
      title: Israel Did Not Accept Correction
      number: 5
      content: "Offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving with leaven,Proclaim and announce
        the freewill offerings;For this you love,You children of Israel!\u201DSays
        the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAlso I gave you cleanness of teeth in all your cities,And lack
        of bread in all your places;Yet you have not returned to Me,\u201DSays the
        Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI also withheld rain from you,When there  were still three
        months to the harvest.I made it rain on one city,I withheld rain from another
        city.One part was rained upon,And where it did not rain the part withered."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So two or three cities wandered to another city to drink water,But
        they were not satisfied;Yet you have not returned to Me,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI blasted you with blight and mildew.When your gardens increased,Your
        vineyards,Your fig trees,And your olive trees,The locust devoured them;Yet
        you have not returned to Me,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI sent among you a plague after the manner of Egypt;Your young
        men I killed with a sword,Along with your captive horses;I made the stench
        of your camps come up into your nostrils;Yet you have not returned to Me,\u201DSays
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI overthrew some of you,As God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah,And
        you were like a firebrand plucked from the burning;Yet you have not returned
        to Me,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus will I do to you, O Israel;Because I will do
        this to you,Prepare to meet your God, O Israel!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For behold,He who forms mountains,And creates the wind,Who declares
        to man what his thought is,And makes the morning darkness,Who treads the
        high places of the earth\u2014The Lord God of hosts is His name."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Lament for Israel'
      title: A Lament for Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Hear this word which I take up against you, a lamentation, O house
        of Israel:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The virgin of Israel has fallen;She will rise no more.She lies forsaken
        on her land;There  is no one to raise her up.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the Lord God:\u201CThe city that goes out by a thousandShall
        have a hundred left,And that which goes out by a hundredShall have ten left
        to the house of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord to the house of Israel:\u201CSeek Me and live;"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But do not seek Bethel,Nor enter Gilgal,Nor pass over to Beersheba;For
        Gilgal shall surely go into captivity,And Bethel shall come to nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Seek the Lord and live,Lest He break out like fire in the house of
        Joseph,And devour it,With no one to quench it in Bethel\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You who turn justice to wormwood,And lay righteousness to rest in
        the earth!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He made the Pleiades and Orion;He turns the shadow of death into morningAnd
        makes the day dark as night;He calls for the waters of the seaAnd pours them
        out on the face of the earth;The Lord  is His name.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He rains ruin upon the strong,So that fury comes upon the fortress.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They hate the one who rebukes in the gate,And they abhor the one who
        speaks uprightly.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Therefore, because you tread down the poorAnd take grain taxes from
        him,Though you have built houses of hewn stone,Yet you shall not dwell in
        them;You have planted pleasant vineyards,But you shall not drink wine from
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For I know your manifold transgressionsAnd your mighty sins:Afflicting
        the just and taking bribes;Diverting the poor from  justice at the gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Therefore the prudent keep silent at that time,For it is an evil time.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Seek good and not evil,That you may live;So the Lord God of hosts
        will be with you,As you have spoken.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Day of the Lord'
      title: The Day of the Lord
      number: 15
      content: Hate evil, love good;Establish justice in the gate.It may be that
        the Lord God of hostsWill be gracious to the remnant of Joseph.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore the Lord God of hosts, the Lord, says this:\u201CThere 
        shall  be wailing in all streets,And they shall say in all the highways,\u2018Alas!
        Alas!\u2019They shall call the farmer to mourning,And skillful lamenters
        to wailing."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "In all vineyards there  shall  be wailing,For I will pass through
        you,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Woe to you who desire the day of the Lord!For what good is  the day
        of the Lord to you?It will  be darkness, and not light.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: It will  be  as though a man fled from a lion,And a bear met him!Or
        as  though he went into the house,Leaned his hand on the wall,And a serpent
        bit him!
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Is not the day of the Lord darkness, and not light?Is  it  not very
        dark, with no brightness in it?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI hate, I despise your feast days,And I do not savor your sacred
        assemblies."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Though you offer Me burnt offerings and your grain offerings,I will
        not accept them,Nor will I regard your fattened peace offerings.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Take away from Me the noise of your songs,For I will not hear the
        melody of your stringed instruments.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But let justice run down like water,And righteousness like a mighty
        stream.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CDid you offer Me sacrifices and offeringsIn the wilderness
        forty years, O house of Israel?"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: You also carried Sikkuth your kingAnd Chiun, your idols,The star of
        your gods,Which you made for yourselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore I will send you into captivity beyond Damascus,\u201DSays
        the Lord, whose name is the God of hosts."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings to Zion and Samaria'
      title: Warnings to Zion and Samaria
      number: 1
      content: Woe to you who  are at ease in Zion,And trust in Mount Samaria,Notable
        persons in the chief nation,To whom the house of Israel comes!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Go over to Calneh and see;And from there go to Hamath the great;Then
        go down to Gath of the Philistines.Are  you better than these kingdoms?Or
        is their territory greater than your territory?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Woe  to you who put far off the day of doom,Who cause the seat of
        violence to come near;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Who lie on beds of ivory,Stretch out on your couches,Eat lambs from
        the flockAnd calves from the midst of the stall;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Who sing idly to the sound of stringed instruments,And invent for
        yourselves musical instruments like David;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Who drink wine from bowls,And anoint yourselves with the best ointments,But
        are not grieved for the affliction of Joseph.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Therefore they shall now go captive as the first of the captives,And
        those who recline at banquets shall be removed.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord God has sworn by Himself,The Lord God of hosts says:\u201CI
        abhor the pride of Jacob,And hate his palaces;Therefore I will deliver up
        the cityAnd all that is in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then it shall come to pass, that if ten men remain in one house,
        they shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And when a relative of  the  dead, with one who will burn the  bodies,
        picks up the bodies to take them out of the house, he will say to one inside
        the house, \u201CAre  there any more with you?\u201DThen someone will say,
        \u201CNone.\u201DAnd he will say, \u201CHold your tongue! For we dare not
        mention the name of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For behold, the Lord gives a command:He will break the great house
        into bits,And the little house into pieces.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Do horses run on rocks?Does one plow there with oxen?Yet you have
        turned justice into gall,And the fruit of righteousness into wormwood,
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You who rejoice over Lo Debar,Who say, \u201CHave we not taken Karnaim
        for ourselvesBy our own strength?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut, behold, I will raise up a nation against you,O house of
        Israel,\u201DSays the Lord God of hosts;\u201CAnd they will afflict you from
        the entrance of HamathTo the Valley of the Arabah.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Locusts'
      title: Vision of the Locusts
      number: 1
      content: "Thus the Lord God showed me: Behold, He formed locust swarms at the
        beginning of the late crop; indeed it  was the late crop after the king\u2019s
        mowings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And so it was, when they had finished eating the grass of the land,
        that I said:\u201CO Lord God, forgive, I pray!Oh, that Jacob may stand,For
        he is small!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Vision of the Fire'
      title: Vision of the Fire
      number: 3
      content: "So  the Lord relented concerning this.\u201CIt shall not be,\u201D
        said the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus the Lord God showed me: Behold, the Lord God called for conflict
        by fire, and it consumed the great deep and devoured the territory.'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I said:\u201CO Lord God, cease, I pray!Oh, that Jacob may stand,For
        he is small!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Vision of the Plumb Line'
      title: Vision of the Plumb Line
      number: 6
      content: "So the Lord relented concerning this.\u201CThis also shall not be,\u201D
        said the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus He showed me: Behold, the Lord stood on a wall made with a plumb
        line, with a plumb line in His hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CAmos, what do you see?\u201DAnd I
        said, \u201CA plumb line.\u201DThen the Lord said:\u201CBehold, I am setting
        a plumb lineIn the midst of My people Israel;I will not pass by them anymore."
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Amaziah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Amaziah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 9
      content: "The high places of Isaac shall be desolate,And the sanctuaries of
        Israel shall be laid waste.I will rise with the sword against the house of
        Jeroboam.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amaziah the priest of Bethel sent to Jeroboam king of Israel,
        saying, \u201CAmos has conspired against you in the midst of the house of
        Israel. The land is not able to bear all his words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus Amos has said:\u2018Jeroboam shall die by the sword,And
        Israel shall surely be led away captiveFrom their own land.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Amaziah said to Amos:\u201CGo, you seer!Flee to the land of
        Judah.There eat bread,And there prophesy."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But never again prophesy at Bethel,For it is the king\u2019s sanctuary,And
        it is the royal residence.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Amos answered, and said to Amaziah:\u201CI was no prophet,Nor
        was I a son of a prophet,But I was a sheepbreederAnd a tender of sycamore
        fruit."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Lord took me as I followed the flock,And the Lord said to
        me,\u2018Go, prophesy to My people Israel.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now therefore, hear the word of the Lord:You say, \u2018Do not prophesy
        against Israel,And do not spout against the house of Isaac.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord:\u2018Your wife shall be a harlot
        in the city;Your sons and daughters shall fall by the sword;Your land shall
        be divided by survey line;You shall die in a defiled land;And Israel shall
        surely be led away captiveFrom his own land.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Vision of the Summer Fruit'
      title: Vision of the Summer Fruit
      number: 1
      content: 'Thus the Lord God showed me: Behold, a basket of summer fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And He said, \u201CAmos, what do you see?\u201DSo I said, \u201CA
        basket of summer fruit.\u201DThen the Lord said to me:\u201CThe end has come
        upon My people Israel;I will not pass by them anymore."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the songs of the templeShall be wailing in that day,\u201DSays
        the Lord God\u2014\u201CMany dead bodies everywhere,They shall be thrown
        out in silence.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Hear this, you who swallow up the needy,And make the poor of the land
        fail,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Saying:\u201CWhen will the New Moon be past,That we may sell grain?And
        the Sabbath,That we may trade wheat?Making the ephah small and the shekel
        large,Falsifying the scales by deceit,"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "That we may buy the poor for silver,And the needy for a pair of sandals\u2014Even
        sell the bad wheat?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord has sworn by the pride of Jacob:\u201CSurely I will never
        forget any of their works."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Shall the land not tremble for this,And everyone mourn who dwells
        in it?All of it shall swell like the River,Heave and subsideLike the River
        of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall come to pass in that day,\u201D says the Lord
        God,\u201CThat I will make the sun go down at noon,And I will darken the
        earth in broad daylight;"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I will turn your feasts into mourning,And all your songs into lamentation;I
        will bring sackcloth on every waist,And baldness on every head;I will make
        it like mourning for an only son,And its end like a bitter day.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord God,\u201CThat
        I will send a famine on the land,Not a famine of bread,Nor a thirst for water,But
        of hearing the words of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They shall wander from sea to sea,And from north to east;They shall
        run to and fro, seeking the word of the Lord,But shall not find it.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIn that day the fair virginsAnd strong young menShall faint
        from thirst."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Those who swear by the sin of Samaria,Who say,\u2018As your god lives,
        O Dan!\u2019And, \u2018As the way of Beersheba lives!\u2019They shall fall
        and never rise again.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Destruction of Israel'
      title: The Destruction of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "I saw the Lord standing by the altar, and He said:\u201CStrike the
        doorposts, that the thresholds may shake,And break them on the heads of them
        all.I will slay the last of them with the sword.He who flees from them shall
        not get away,And he who escapes from them shall not be delivered."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThough they dig into hell,From there My hand shall take them;Though
        they climb up to heaven,From there I will bring them down;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And though they hide themselves on top of Carmel,From there I will
        search and take them;Though they hide from My sight at the bottom of the
        sea,From there I will command the serpent, and it shall bite them;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Though they go into captivity before their enemies,From there I will
        command the sword,And it shall slay them.I will set My eyes on them for harm
        and not for good.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord God of hosts,He who touches the earth and it melts,And all
        who dwell there mourn;All of it shall swell like the River,And subside like
        the River of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He who builds His layers in the sky,And has founded His strata in
        the earth;Who calls for the waters of the sea,And pours them out on the face
        of the earth\u2014The Lord  is His name."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAre you not like the people of Ethiopia to Me,O children of
        Israel?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CDid I not bring up Israel from the land
        of Egypt,The Philistines from Caphtor,And the Syrians from Kir?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, the eyes of the Lord God  are on the sinful kingdom,And
        I will destroy it from the face of the earth;Yet I will not utterly destroy
        the house of Jacob,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor surely I will command,And will sift the house of Israel
        among all nations,As grain is sifted in a sieve;Yet not the smallest grain
        shall fall to the ground."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Israel Will Be Restored'
      title: Israel Will Be Restored
      number: 10
      content: "All the sinners of My people shall die by the sword,Who say, \u2018The
        calamity shall not overtake nor confront us.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201COn that day I will raise upThe tabernacle of David, which has
        fallen down,And repair its damages;I will raise up its ruins,And rebuild
        it as in the days of old;"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "That they may possess the remnant of Edom,And all the Gentiles who
        are called by My name,\u201DSays the Lord who does this thing."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWhen
        the plowman shall overtake the reaper,And the treader of grapes him who sows
        seed;The mountains shall drip with sweet wine,And all the hills shall flow
        with  it."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I will bring back the captives of My people Israel;They shall build
        the waste cities and inhabit them;They shall plant vineyards and drink wine
        from them;They shall also make gardens and eat fruit from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will plant them in their land,And no longer shall they be pulled
        upFrom the land I have given them,\u201DSays the Lord your God."
      comments: []
